title: Most Maine graphic ever shows moose-car collisions for past year - Maine news
text:
The Portland Press Herald has released arguably the most Maine interactive graphic, which shows every moose-vehicle collision in the past year.
 The Portland Press Herald According to the Press Herald , there were 327 moose-vehicle collisions in the measured time period, 55 of which resulted in human injuries, and one of which resulted in a human death.
It’s unclear how many of the crashes resulted in moose fatalities.
The study does show that June is the highest month for moose-based collisions, and that there wasn’t a single reported moose-car crash in March 2015.
